It seems like it should. Maybe I can make it unconditional for Ddeml in the test resources. However, the main condition for metadata shouldn't be altered. For proper coverage, we have to address all public fields, but we need to ensure `getInt` is called. I think we might need to use a fake library, which means editing the test should be next on my list!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jWUivgaqi6ZBhOU3pcgvjBxr|fc_0bbb39c135ee2d310169f9850ee3b08196ba87ac9b3b0a8fa4", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.java.dev.jna/jna-platform/5.3.1/src/test/java/net_java_dev_jna/jna_platform/DdemlUtilInnerDdemlExceptionTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "package net_java_dev_jna.jna_platform;\n\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.DdemlUtil;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n", "newText": "package net_java_dev_jna.jna_platform;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport com.sun.jna.NativeLibrary;\nimport com.sun.jna.Platform;\nimport com.sun.jna.platform.win32.DdemlUtil;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertEquals;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void createBuildsExceptionForDdemlErrorCode() {\n        try {\n            DdemlUtil.DdemlException exception = DdemlUtil.DdemlException.create(\n                    DMLERR_BUSY);\n\n            String message = exception.getMessage();\n\n            assertEquals(DMLERR_BUSY, exception.getErrorCode());\n            assertTrue(message.contains(\"Code: 0x4001\"));\n            assertTrue(message.contains(\"DMLERR_BUSY\"));\n        } catch (UnsatisfiedLinkError error) {\n            assertDdemlNativeLibraryUnavailable(error);\n        } catch (ExceptionInInitializerError error) {\n            assertDdemlNativeLibraryUnavailable(error.getCause());\n        } catch (NoClassDefFoundError error) {\n            assertDdemlNativeLibraryUnavailable(error);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void assertDdemlNativeLibraryUnavailable(Throwable error) {\n        assertTrue(\n                describesUser32Library(error) || describesDdemlInitializationFailure(error),\n                () -> \"Unexpected DDEML initialization failure: \" + error);\n    }\n\n    private static boolean describesUser32Library(Throwable error) {\n        for (Throwable current = error; current != null; current = current.getCause()) {\n            if (String.valueOf(current.getMessage()).contains(\"user32\")) {\n                return true;\n            }\n        }\n        return false;\n    }\n\n    private static boolean describesDdemlInitializationFailure(Throwable error) {\n        return error instanceof NoClassDefFoundError\n                && String.valueOf(error.getMessage())\n                        .contains(\"com.sun.jna.platform.win32.Ddeml\");\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void createBuildsExceptionForDdemlErrorCode(@TempDir Path tempDirectory) throws IOException {\n        prepareUser32Alias(tempDirectory);\n\n        DdemlUtil.DdemlException exception = DdemlUtil.DdemlException.create(DMLERR_BUSY);\n        String message = exception.getMessage();\n\n        assertEquals(DMLERR_BUSY, exception.getErrorCode());\n        assertTrue(message.contains(\"Code: 0x4001\"));\n        assertTrue(message.contains(\"DMLERR_BUSY\"));\n    }\n\n    private static void prepareUser32Alias(Path tempDirectory) throws IOException {\n        if (Platform.isWindows()) {\n            return;\n        }\n\n        Path source = findLoadableSystemLibrary();\n        Path alias = tempDirectory.resolve(System.mapLibraryName(\"user32\"));\n        try {\n            Files.createSymbolicLink(alias, source);\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException | IOException error) {\n            Files.copy(source, alias);\n        }\n        NativeLibrary.addSearchPath(\"user32\", tempDirectory.toString());\n    }\n\n    private static Path findLoadableSystemLibrary() {\n        List<Path> candidates = List.of(\n                Path.of(\"/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6\"),\n                Path.of(\"/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6\"),\n                Path.of(\"/lib64/libc.so.6\"),\n                Path.of(\"/usr/lib64/libc.so.6\"),\n                Path.of(\"/usr/lib/libSystem.B.dylib\"));\n        for (Path candidate : candidates) {\n            if (Files.isRegularFile(candidate)) {\n                return candidate;\n            }\n        }\n        throw new IllegalStateException(\"No loadable system library found for user32 alias\");\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1443, "output": 2577, "cacheRead": 55296, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59316, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777960185735, "responseId": "resp_0bbb39c135ee2d310169f984fa5ce08196a5cad0225e9a6058"}}
